<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 05 at 5:41AM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...CAUTIOUS TRAVEL IS ADVISED FOR SNOW-COVERED ROADWAYS THIS
MORNING...
WEATHER...
* Light snow will continue across portions of Southeast Michigan
through daybreak.
* A dusting of snow can be expected through 8 AM this morning.
IMPACTS...
* Snow accumulations have led to snow covered roadways across
Southeast Michigan this morning.
* Light Snow is not expected to cause a widespread reduction in
visibility.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* The combination of light snow and cold temperatures will result
in slippery conditions and variable traffic rates throughout
the county. Motorists are urged to use caution and account for
the variable driving conditions by allowing extra time.
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
